text: All was good until my daughter got accepted into pre k in the county. We were told we could do a day to day pay for the 1 week that we needed her to go there  until she started school. That Monday I was told that my child could not PAY... the day to day charge or for the one week and was basically turned away. My child has been going this daycare/pre k for over 2yrs and this was the treatment we get when she's accepted into school and not their pre k that charges every week... Did really she why they would turn away money.

text: We were greeted with smiles, hand shakes and hugs! Bible Study was great and we loved the message. Not just for others to hear us...but for us to hear you all. Tears flowed, praises were given to God and love was shared. Sounds like family to me! Can't wait to fellowship with y'all again. With much love and respect.

text:
I have had my 2 children, now 3 and 5 at Christ the King preschool since both were infants and there is no where else I would rather have them. The teachers and the administrators are the best and there is a loving Christ filled atmosphere.
I would reccomend anyone who is looking for child care to use them.

I personally am not a member here, but find myself inside these doors several nights out of the week to fellowship and enjoy community.
